			<p>The salient engineering contribution of Aria-Duet is a *continuous prefill* strategy: rather than computing the full KV cache in one operation at handover time, the system divides the growing context into chunks and fills the cache incrementally while the human is still playing. By the time the pedal is pressed, the cache is already warm, reducing the perceived gap from approximately 1.8 seconds to roughly 150ms of speculative re-evaluation.</p>
